    "Abstract": {
      "AbstractText": [
        "This paper discusses ideas about depression as a paradigmatic symptom of contemporaneous psychological suffering and makes a comparison between depression and melancholia. The ideas we describe were stimulated by two comparative studies that were conducted based on an\u00a0analysis of how depressed subjects\u00a0relate to the concept of desire, their feelings of shame and their self-image in today's age."
      ]
